Description. Body length: 2.88–3.66 mm , holotype 3.25 mm (
Fig. 13
).

Antennae robust. Scape in basal part S-shaped curved, first curvature just at base, second in about basal third. Scape in apical two thirds weakly gradually enlarged to apex, about as wide as club or protibia at midlength. Funicle short, segment 1 robust, 1.2–1.3 times as long as wide and 1.6–1.7 times as long as short segment 2 , which is isodiametric; segments 3–6 1.2–1.3 times as wide as long, segment 7 1.4–1.5 times as wide as long. Club 1.6–1.7 times as long as wide (
Fig. 17
).

Female genitalia. Sternite VIII with slender and long, umbrella-shaped plate, apically elongated to slender tip; apodeme with distinct caput, terminated inside of plate and almost reaching its point, about equally long as plate. Gonocoxites large, flat, subtrapezoid, with slender long apical stylus. Spermatheca with distinct rounded caput, long ramus and shorter, distinctly slenderer, tube-shaped nodulus; cornu moderately long, regularly curved (
Fig. 36
).
